'From Squeak3.6gamma of ''11 September 2003'' [latest update: #5421] on 17 October 2003 at 9:43:41 am'!"Change Set:		ansiAssignmentOp-brpDate:			17 October 2003Author:			Brent PinkneyThis change set adds a new preference to Squeak to control whether the assignment operator is displayed as a _ or as a :=.This preference only takes effect if browseWithPrettyPrint is true."!!AssignmentNode methodsFor: 'printing' stamp: 'brp 10/8/2003 14:55'!printOn: aStream indent: level 	aStream dialect = #SQ00		ifTrue: [aStream				withStyleFor: #setOrReturn				do: [aStream nextPutAll: 'Set '].			variable printOn: aStream indent: level.			aStream				withStyleFor: #setOrReturn				do: [aStream nextPutAll: ' to '].			value printOn: aStream indent: level + 2]		ifFalse: [variable printOn: aStream indent: level.			aStream				nextPutAll: (Preferences ansiAssignmentOperatorWhenPrettyPrinting						ifTrue: [' := ']						ifFalse: [' _ ']).			value printOn: aStream indent: level + 2]! !!Preferences class methodsFor: 'standard queries'!ansiAssignmentOperatorWhenPrettyPrinting	^ self		valueOfFlag: #ansiAssignmentOperatorWhenPrettyPrinting		ifAbsent: [true]! !"Postscript:This postcript installs the new preference"Preferences	addPreference: #ansiAssignmentOperatorWhenPrettyPrinting	category: #browsing 	default: true	balloonHelp: 'If true, then when browseWithPrettyPrint is in effect, the assignment operator will be presented as :='.!